    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-12-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="197" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Lord Lyons</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-12-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 16, 1861.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have this afternoon had the honor to
                            receive two notes from you dated thirteen days ago, and a third dated
                            twelve days ago. They relate to the representations which I felt it to
                            be my duty to address to you with regard to the <pb facs="0312" n="242" xml:id="pg_242"/> treatment to which seamen belonging to the British
                            schooners Revere and Louisa Agnes were subjected by officers of the
                            United States navy. It is not my purpose, on the present occasion, to
                            make any observations on their contents. I hasten, however, to inform
                            you that they have only reached me to-day, lest I should be deemed
                            guilty of discourtesy in not having acknowledged the receipt of them
                            until so long after their dates.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with high consideration, sir, your most obedient,
                            humble servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>LYONS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
